feat(§17.103): ImportExportServiceV4 + TreeCodecV4 port

Fourteenth execution strand of the §17.94 v5 round-7 plan and the
seventh Phase C strand (Phase C.4). Closes Phase C entirely — every
v3 application service now has a parallel-additive v4 successor.

Behavioural clone of v3's ImportExportService modulo the Tree type
substitution; validate-before-replace contract preserved byte-for-byte
(decode FIRST, throw on malformed/invalid input, only successful
decode calls replaceCurrentTree; failure leaves the current tree
untouched). Callable-decoupling pattern stays — the service knows
nothing about boards/ids/persistence layout.

What this strand does:
- NEW src/application/ports/TreeCodecV4.ts: TreeCodecV4 interface
  with encode(tree: Tree): string + decode(text: string): Tree;
  same throw/no-throw contract as v3.
- NEW src/application/ImportExportServiceV4.ts: 2 public methods
  (exportCurrentTree + importIntoCurrentBoard) + 1 private static
  errorReason; constructor takes TreeCodecV4 + getCurrentTree +
  replaceCurrentTree callables (wired by the composition root).
- NEW ImportExportServiceV4.test.ts: 4 combined-assertion tests
  compressing v3's 7-test surface — export happy + no-caching;
  import happy + decode-before-replace ordering (vi.fn event
  recording); import failure modes (malformed JSON + unknown id +
  replace-throw all in one); round-trip preservation.

What this strand does NOT do:
- Doesn't wire ImportExportServiceV4 into main.ts (§17.110 Phase E).
- Doesn't add jsonCodecV4 adapter (§17.105 decode + §17.106 encode).
- Doesn't touch v3 ImportExportService (retires at §17.111).
- Doesn't bridge v3/v4 wire formats (each codec speaks its own dialect).

Sonar: projectVersion bump 0.2.26 → 0.2.27. Bundle delta: 0
(both new files tree-shaken until §17.110).

Tests: 1107 → 1111 unit (+4 net combined-assertion). 116 e2e unchanged.
Lint clean.
